oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Westminster Abbey, interior, London
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Interior of Westminster Abbey looking towards the altar.

Originally a monastery built approximately 960 and was expanded by Edward the Confessor in approximately 1040s. Consecrated 28 December 1065. Rebuilt in 13th century by Henry III. Burial site for kings and queens. Site for every coronation since 1066.
